$ $ORACLE_HOME/install/utl/rootinstall.sh

`$ORACLE_HOME/install/utl/rootinstall.sh` is called by `→ Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/root_sh`.

`rootinstall_sh`
  • copies → Linux/fhs/usr/local/bin/oraenv[`oraenv`], `corenv` and → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/bin/dbhome[`dbhome`] to the directory pointed at with the environment variable `LBIN` (typically `→ Linux/fhs/usr/local/bin`)
  • creates `→ Linux/fhs/etc/oratab` (if it doesn't already exist)
